          "id": "649d712ceca2fbc00851770d0aebcdc7c5badc58",
          "message": "[UI] Scope ATOM watermark to Performance tab only (#524)\n\n* [UI] Scope ATOM watermark to Performance tab only\n\nReplace global Chart.js watermark with Performance-tab-scoped guard.\nOther tabs (Tradeoff, Trends, Data, Accuracy, Competitive) now render\nclean without watermark overlay.\n\nCherry-picked from ROCm/AI-Frameworks-Dashboard#32\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n* [UI] Add watermark overlay to dashboard tables\n\nAdd CSS ::after pseudo-element on .table-watermark to render ATOM logo\nwatermark on performance tables. Reverts the Chart.js guard from the\nprevious commit — chart watermarks remain on all tabs as before.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n* fix: use data-URI watermark with background-attachment fixed\n\nReplace ::after pseudo-element approach (invisible due to overflow\nclipping) with pre-processed 8%-alpha logo as data URI embedded in\nCSS background. Uses background-attachment:fixed for viewport-centered\npositioning with zero scroll lag.\n\nSplit table-watermark into outer wrapper + inner scroll container\nto keep watermark visible while allowing horizontal table scroll.\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nCo-authored-by: Lingpeng Jin <103567126+valarLip@users.noreply.github.com>",
